 more may die due to the cold and lack of shelter and essential winter supplies. Displaced Palestinians are living in tents made of cloth and nylon, amidst harsh humanitarian conditions due to the scarcity of basic life necessities such as water and food, as well as a severe shortage of clothing, blankets, and heating means during the winter. They have resorted to tents after Israel destroyed their homes and forced them to leave their residential areas and head to regions south of the Netzarim axis in southern Gaza, which the occupying army established at the beginning of its ground operation in the area on October 27, 2023. According to estimates from the Gaza government media office, the number of displaced persons in the Gaza Strip has reached about two million out of the 2.4 million residing in the region. With American support, Israel has been committing genocide in Gaza since October 7, 2023, resulting in more than 154,000 Palestinian martyrs and wounded, most of whom are children and women, and over 11,000 missing, amidst massive destruction and an unprecedented humanitarian catastrophe."}
